	(text "LoRa Telemetry - MAIN board (DevKitC-1 + power block)\nShared design: identical for TX and RX (order 2 copies).\nStacks with a matching RF board (tx_rf or rx_rf) directly on top:\nJ4 here is a FEMALE socket (top side, like the DevKit socket);\nthe RF board's matching MALE header is mounted on ITS back side,\nso the RF board sits right-side-up directly above main, pins\nplugging down - no flipping, nothing sandwiched. The RF board's\nbutton/LED (and RX's OLED) are broken out via jumper wires since\nthey need to stay human-accessible once stacked. Cross-sheet nets\nuse global labels (VSYS, E22_VCC, +3V3, GND, and everything the\nRF board needs)." (at 12.7 70 0) (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5))) (uuid "e9fd7ace-c6f8-4731-9c28-c9daea78c185"))
